The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | BHA president to enter IHF race
                                                   BHA president to enter IHF race
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The Bengal Hockey Association (BHA) president, J.B. Roy is all set to throw his hat in the ring for the post of the Indian Hockey Federation (IHF) president. He is expected to make an announcement in the next couple of days.         
	According to sources, Roy is already in touch with top hockey officials, including senior members of the Indian Olympic Association (IOA) ad hoc committee. The BHA president belongs to Sahara India, the sponsors of the Indian hockey team.         
	Roy has the support of at least 28 state associations and will seek their votes whenever the elections are announced, sources said.         
	When asked, an ad hoc committee member refused to comment on the issue.                                                                                                                       
